`README.md`:

```md
# DEep Learning for BOT detection by Mouse movements (DELBOT Mouse)

This repository is a small TypeScript library to distinguish humans and bots from their mouse movements with
the usage of [TensorFlow.js](https://www.tensorflow.org/js). It was initiated by an internship with the
[Bureau404](https://www.bureau404.fr) company as part of the Master's in Mathematics:
Specialist Focus on Careers in Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence ([University of Mons](https://web.umons.ac.be/fr/))

- Author : Christophe Grandmont.
- Internship supervisor (Bureau404) : Loïc Jean-Fulcrand ([website](https://www.malt.ch/profile/loicjeanfulcrand))
- Internship supervisor (UMONS) : Christophe Troestler ([website](https://staff.umons.ac.be/christophe.troestler/))

## About

Delbot Mouse is a prototype open-source tool using [TensorFlow.js](https://www.tensorflow.org/js) and some more
other libraries like RandomForest to develop a generic way to distinguish humans and bots from their mouse movements on
a web page. The repository contains three distinct JavaScript or Typescript modules:

1. delbot-core: the core of the library that contains everything to load an existing model and use it.
2. delbot-training: the part of the code using delbot-core to train new models from scratch. It also contains a 
   Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) implementation to generate bot trajectories.
3. delbot-example: example of usage of delbot-core and delbot-training to train new models or use one.

We also have a `python/` folder being the script location to manipulate data.

Delbot-core:
[![npm version](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse?color=33cd56&logo=npm)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse)

Delbot-training:
[![npm version](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/@chrisgdt/delbot-training?color=33cd56&logo=npm)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@chrisgdt/delbot-training)


## How to install

### For Node
You can install delbot-core or delbot-training from NPM for Node with:
```
npm install @chrisgdt/delbot-mouse
```
```
npm install @chrisgdt/delbot-training
```

You will also need to install TensorFlow, we let you chose the version.
```
npm install @tensorflow/tfjs
```

__Notice that Delbot Mouse is initially meant to be used in the web browser__. Using Node.js or other
JavaScript engines might lead to some unknown errors that you can report here as issue.

### For the browser
For a browser usage, you can simply add some script tags. To load delbot-mouse, you need TensorFlow.js.
```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tensorflow/tfjs@4.0.0/dist/tf.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse@1.1.2/dist/delbot.js"></script>
```

To load  delbot-training, you need both Tensorflow.js and delbot-training, and it is highly encouraged to load tfjs-vis
for training visualization.
```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tensorflow/tfjs@4.0.0/dist/tf.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tensorflow/tfjs-vis@1.5.1/dist/tfjs-vis.umd.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse@1.1.2/dist/delbot.js"></script>
<script src=" https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@chrisgdt/delbot-training@1.1.2/dist/delbot-training.js"></script>
```

## How to use

With Node, you can import delbot with `import * as delbot from "@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse";`.

If needed, you can also import tensorFlow with `import * as tf from '@tensorflow/tfjs';`.

To import delbot-training, use `import * as delbotrain from "@chrisgdt/delbot-training";`.

---

For browser, once you have loaded delbot mouse with the script tag, everything is packed in the single variable
`delbot`, same for the variable `delbotrain` with delbot-training. Everything is exported from `src/index.ts`, check the
[doc of delbot-core](https://chrisgdt.github.io/DELBOT-Mouse/delbot-core/docs/modules/index.html) or the
[doc of delbot-training](https://chrisgdt.github.io/DELBOT-Mouse/delbot-training/docs/modules/index.html) for more information.

The folder `trained-models/` contains some pre-trained models that you can use easily from delbot-core with, for example,
`delbot.Models.rnn3`.

Otherwise, you have an entire example of usage without the training in `/delbot-example/` [here](https://chrisgdt.github.io/DELBOT-Mouse/delbot-example/src/index.html).


## Basic usage - Example

```ts
import * as delbot from "@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse"; // not needed in browser

// Create an empty recorder to store and compute mouse features
// Set the screen size to normalize (x,y) positions in [0,1]^2
recorder = new Recorder(window.screen.width, window.screen.height);

// Set max size to prevent high memory usage
recorder.setMaxSize(1e6);

// For each small movement, store it in the recorder
document.addEventListener("mousemove", event => {
  recorder.addRecord({
    time: event.timeStamp,
    x: event.clientX,
    y: event.clientY,
    type: "Move" // optional
  });
});

myVerifyElement.addEventListener("click", event => {
  if (recorder.getRecords().length > 100) {
    // Models are obtained from delbot.Models
    const isHuman = recorder.isHuman(delbot.Models.rnn1);
    recorder.clearRecord();
    // ...
  }
});
```

## Training

Here some example and explanations about the training of new models.

### Models

Some pre-trained models are available through `delbot.Models` :

- rnn1 : a neural network with two LSTM layers, the most efficient so far.
- rrn1faster : same, but with less LSTM cells, slightly less efficient.
- rnn2 : same, but the second LSTM layer is replaced by a dense layer.
- rnn3 : a model between rnn1 and rnn3, two LSTM layers then one dense.
- denseMatrix : a neural network with only dense layers and that takes a movement matrix.
- convolutional : a convolutional model that takes a movement matrix.
- randomForest : a random forest machine learning model.

To train your own model with custom tfjs layers, you can look at `delbot-training/src/models.ts` and read
the documentation. You only have to extend a class and define a single method.

You also have a GAN architecture in `delbot-training/src/GANtrain.ts`.

### Dataset

To manipulate the dataset, you can use `python/` folder, here is a short description of each python script.
- parseSample.py : takes some folders with text files of either bot or human trajectories and parse them to a single
                session.json file containing all relative paths to those text files. This JSON file is the entry
                of an instance of dataTraining.
- redraw.py : verifies that text trajectories in a folder is what we except by drawing them with matplotlib.
- botDrawing.py : starts python selenium and draw same shapes from arbitrary heuristics and multiple librairies.
- ganParser.py : takes some GAN folder of generator ouputs and parse them to something readable by `parseSample.py`.

For the dataset usage in the training itself, unzip the file `dataset.tar.gz` to obtain multiple data folder inside
`python/`, then run `parseSample.py` to get `sessions.json` (for normal training) and `sessions_human_only.json` (for GAN).

⚠️ The dataset is relatively limited: it contains only a small set of human trajectories, along with
trajectories generated by different algorithms / programs created for that purpose or found online.


### Example

The code of a basic training looks like this :
```ts
const data = new delbot.data.DataFeatures2({xSize: 24, numClasses: 2});
const filePath = "../../python/sessions.json"; // path from code to session.json

const datatraining = new delbotrain.DataTraining({filePath: filePath, data: data});

const rnn1Features2 = new delbotrain.ModelRNN({
  dataTraining: datatraining,
  nameToSave: "downloads://model-rnn1-features2", // directly use layerModel.save(nameToSave)
  epoch: 25,
  batchSize: 256,
  useTfjsVis: true,
  consoleInfo: true
});
// or simply 'rfFeature2.run()'
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {rfFeature2.run()});
```

And for a GAN training :
```ts
// DataSimplePosition: output (x,y) for each movement
const data = new delbot.data.DataSimplePosition({xSize: 35, numClasses: 1});
const filePath = "../../python/sessions_human_only.json"; // path from code to sessions_human_only.json

const datatraining = new delbotrain.DataTraining({
  filePath: filePath,
  data: data,
  trainingRatio: .9 // use 90% of the dataset as training set and 10% as validation
});

// Delay for tfjs-vis used in constructor
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  const gan = new delbotrain.GAN({
    dataTraining: datatraining, // xSize is 35 so the generator outputs 35 movements per trajectories
    epoch: 1000,
    batchSize: 64,
    generatorSeedSize: 100, // generator input is 100 random numbers
    useTfjsVis: true,
    consoleInfo: true,
    downloadModels: 50, // save models every 50 epochs
    downloadSample: true
  });

  gan.train(1); // training number 1 to have unique ID per GAN train
});
```

@keyframes fade-in {
    from {
        opacity: 0;
    }
    to {
        opacity: 1;
    }
}
@keyframes fade-out {
    from {
        opacity: 1;
        visibility: visible;
    }
    to {
        opacity: 0;
    }
}
@keyframes fade-in-delayed {
    0% {
        opacity: 0;
    }
    33% {
        opacity: 0;
    }
    100% {
        opacity: 1;
    }
}
@keyframes fade-out-delayed {
    0% {
        opacity: 1;
        visibility: visible;
    }
    66% {
        opacity: 0;
    }
    100% {
        opacity: 0;
    }
}
@keyframes shift-to-left {
    from {
        transform: translate(0, 0);
    }
    to {
        transform: translate(-25%, 0);
    }
}
@keyframes unshift-to-left {
    from {
        transform: translate(-25%, 0);
    }
    to {
        transform: translate(0, 0);
    }
}
@keyframes pop-in-from-right {
    from {
        transform: translate(100%, 0);
    }
    to {
        transform: translate(0, 0);
    }
}
@keyframes pop-out-to-right {
    from {
        transform: translate(0, 0);
        visibility: visible;
    }
    to {
        transform: translate(100%, 0);
    }
}

<div class="tsd-page-title">
<ul class="tsd-breadcrumb">
<li><a href="../modules.html">@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse</a></li>
<li><a href="../modules/data.html">data</a></li>
<li><a href="data.Data.html">Data</a></li></ul>
<h1>Class Data<code class="tsd-tag ts-flagAbstract">Abstract</code> </h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An abstract class that extracts some mouse features from <a href="recording.Recorder.html">Recorder</a>
and format them with <a href="data.Data.html#loadDataSet">loadDataSet</a> to create an input of a tf.js model.
This input is an array, but you can call tf.tensor3d and tf.reshape
to get the tensor. It is always a 3D tensor, each element of the dataset being a matrix
<a href="data.Data.html#xSize">xSize</a> x <a href="data.Data.html#ySize">ySize</a>.
<br>
You can also specify an integer <code>userIndex</code> to work with labels for training.
While dataset is a 3D array with the first dimension representing the size of the dataset,
labels are represented by a 2D array with the same first dimension and the second one
is the label of the corresponding sample.
<br>
The field <a href="data.Data.html#numClasses">numClasses</a> can be 1 or 2. You can ignore it and let the default value to 2.
If you want more details: as 1, if a model is constructed with <code>delbot-training</code>, it
will have a single neuron as output and <code>binaryCrossentropy</code> loss function, each label
during the training will be a singleton [0] or [1] for respectively human and bot, the
model then outputs the probability [p] for the sample to be a bot. If there are two classes,
the loss function is <code>categoricalCrossentropy</code> for two neurons, the labels are [1,0] or
[0,1] for respectively human and bot samples and outputs from the model are [1-p,p] where p
is the probability to be a bot.
<br>
Extend this class and implement the method <a href="data.Data.html#loadDataSet">loadDataSet</a> to create your own logic and
data format. Your implementation has to look something like 1. empty data and label
arrays, 2. iterate through <a href="recording.Recorder.html#getRecords">getRecords</a> and 3. add labels userIndex is positive.
You can also check if <a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#type">type</a> is null or includes &quot;Move&quot; to filter only
move actions.</p>
</div></section>

<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> <span>add<wbr/>Label</span><a href="#addLabel" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="addLabel.addLabel-1">add<wbr/>Label<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span><a href="#addLabel.addLabel-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> 
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Gets the current array of labels from a dataset and append a new
label according to the number of classes <a href="data.Data.html#numClasses">numClasses</a>.
If there is one class, [0] means human and [1] bot while with
two classes, [1,0] means human and [0,1] bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>datasetLabels: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The current dataset label array, we add an element to it.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class, 0 for human and 1 for bot.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="loadDataSet" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagAbstract">Abstract</code> <span>load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set</span><a href="#loadDataSet" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1">load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>recorder<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span><a href="#loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>This method gets a recorder object and loads it as a Dataset object
with the right format. The return value might contain empty arrays if the
recorder as too few elements. The userIndex is an integer that says what is the
class index for the label, in our case of binary classifier human-bot, 0 means
human and 1 means bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>recorder: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The recorder containing loaded records and features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagOptional">Optional</code> userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class from record, if unspecified or negative,
                 the label array of the return object is empty.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span></h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameters">
<li class="tsd-parameter">

<li class="tsd-parameter">

<div class="tsd-page-title">

<li><a href="data.DataFeatures.html">DataFeatures</a></li></ul>
<h1>Class DataFeatures</h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>A Data class that represents chunks of mouse features selected from
the <a href="recording.Recorder.html">Recorder</a> object. The field <a href="data.DataFeatures.html#xSize">xSize</a> is the chunk size,
default to 24, and <a href="data.DataFeatures.html#ySize">ySize</a> the number of extracted features.
<br>
The dataset there is a list of chunks of mouse features.
<br>
It can be the case that a chunk is not fully complete after reading the
record, if the field <a href="data.DataFeatures.html#shouldCompleteXSize">shouldCompleteXSize</a> is set to true, we complete
it with trailing zeros.
<br>
This class takes 8 features :</p>
<ol>
  <li><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#dx">dx</a></li>
  <li><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#dy">dy</a></li>
  <li><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#speedX">speedX</a></li>
  <li><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#speedY">speedY</a></li>
  <li><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#speed">speed</a></li>
  <li><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#accel">accel</a></li>
  <li><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#distance">distance</a></li>
  <li><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html#timeDiff">timeDiff</a></li>
</ol>
<h3>See</h3><p>Data</p>
</div></section>

<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> <span>may<wbr/>Normalize<wbr/>Data</span><a href="#mayNormalizeData" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>

<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Boolean to know if we may normalize data. If false, then
data must not be normalized, otherwise some operations
of the model will fail.</p>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-property tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited"><a id="xSize" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> <span>x<wbr/>Size</span><a href="#xSize" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited"><a id="addLabel" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> <span>add<wbr/>Label</span><a href="#addLabel" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="addLabel.addLabel-1">add<wbr/>Label<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span><a href="#addLabel.addLabel-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> 
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Gets the current array of labels from a dataset and append a new
label according to the number of classes <a href="data.DataFeatures.html#numClasses">numClasses</a>.
If there is one class, [0] means human and [1] bot while with
two classes, [1,0] means human and [0,1] bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>datasetLabels: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The current dataset label array, we add an element to it.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class, 0 for human and 1 for bot.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="loadDataSet" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set</span><a href="#loadDataSet" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1">load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>recorder<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span><a href="#loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>This method gets a recorder object and loads it as a Dataset object
with the right format. The return value might contain empty arrays if the
recorder as too few elements. The userIndex is an integer that says what is the
class index for the label, in our case of binary classifier human-bot, 0 means
human and 1 means bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>recorder: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The recorder containing loaded records and features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = -1</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class from record, if unspecified or negative,
                 the label array of the return object is empty.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span></h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameters">
<li class="tsd-parameter">
<h5>dataset<wbr/>Data<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5></li>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited"><a id="addLabel" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> <span>add<wbr/>Label</span><a href="#addLabel" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="addLabel.addLabel-1">add<wbr/>Label<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span><a href="#addLabel.addLabel-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> 
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Gets the current array of labels from a dataset and append a new
label according to the number of classes <a href="data.DataFeatures2.html#numClasses">numClasses</a>.
If there is one class, [0] means human and [1] bot while with
two classes, [1,0] means human and [0,1] bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>datasetLabels: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The current dataset label array, we add an element to it.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class, 0 for human and 1 for bot.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-inherited"><a id="loadDataSet" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set</span><a href="#loadDataSet" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-inherited">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1">load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>recorder<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span><a href="#loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>This method gets a recorder object and loads it as a Dataset object
with the right format. The return value might contain empty arrays if the
recorder as too few elements. The userIndex is an integer that says what is the
class index for the label, in our case of binary classifier human-bot, 0 means
human and 1 means bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>recorder: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The recorder containing loaded records and features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = -1</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class from record, if unspecified or negative,
                 the label array of the return object is empty.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span></h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameters">
<li class="tsd-parameter">
<h5>dataset<wbr/>Data<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5></li>

<h1>Class DataMovementMatrix</h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>A Data class that represents a movement matrix. For each step N of <a href="data.DataMovementMatrix.html#steps">steps</a>
we create a 0-matrix <a href="data.DataMovementMatrix.html#xMaxMov">xMaxMov</a>-<a href="data.DataMovementMatrix.html#xMinMov">xMinMov</a> x <a href="data.DataMovementMatrix.html#yMaxMov">yMaxMov</a>-<a href="data.DataMovementMatrix.html#yMinMov">yMinMov</a>
and add a small number at position (dx,dy) for at most N trajectories, where
dx = x(n) - x(n-1) is the pixel offset in x coordinate between two recorded movements
in the trajectory. We repeat that until there are no sample left, then for the next N.
<br>
If a value should be outside the matrix, we put it on the edge. The default size
is 50x50 (range -25 to 25) and default steps are [25, 50, 100, 150, 200, 250].</p>

<h3>See</h3><p>Data</p>
</div></section>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited"><a id="addLabel" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> <span>add<wbr/>Label</span><a href="#addLabel" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="addLabel.addLabel-1">add<wbr/>Label<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span><a href="#addLabel.addLabel-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> 
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Gets the current array of labels from a dataset and append a new
label according to the number of classes <a href="data.DataMovementMatrix.html#numClasses">numClasses</a>.
If there is one class, [0] means human and [1] bot while with
two classes, [1,0] means human and [0,1] bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>datasetLabels: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The current dataset label array, we add an element to it.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class, 0 for human and 1 for bot.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<p>Inherited from <a href="data.Data.html">Data</a>.<a href="data.Data.html#addLabel">addLabel</a></p>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-private"><a id="getInRangeForArray" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagPrivate">Private</code> <span>get<wbr/>In<wbr/>Range<wbr/>For<wbr/>Array</span><a href="#getInRangeForArray" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-private">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="getInRangeForArray.getInRangeForArray-1">get<wbr/>In<wbr/>Range<wbr/>For<wbr/>Array<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>min<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span>, max<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span>, value<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><a href="#getInRangeForArray.getInRangeForArray-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagPrivate">Private</code> 
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Force the value to stand in <code>[0, max-min[</code> for index of matrix, so
min is the first index 0 and max the last index. If the value is
greater than max or less than min, we consider the bound.</p>

<h3>Returns</h3><p>The value in the new integer domain starting from 0.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>min: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An integer, lower bound of initial domain.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>max: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An integer, upper bound of initial domain.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>value: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An integer, the value to constraint.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/data.ts#L193">src/data.ts:193</a></li></ul></aside></li></ul></section>

<li class="tsd-description"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagPrivate">Private</code> 
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Get integer neighbours of the given value within a distance of range and
return a list of unique elements of this neighbourhood (in case the value
is on an edge, there will be less than range squared values).</p>
</div>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="loadDataSet" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set</span><a href="#loadDataSet" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1">load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>recorder<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span><a href="#loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>This method gets a recorder object and loads it as a Dataset object
with the right format. The return value might contain empty arrays if the
recorder as too few elements. The userIndex is an integer that says what is the
class index for the label, in our case of binary classifier human-bot, 0 means
human and 1 means bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>recorder: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The recorder containing loaded records and features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = -1</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class from record, if unspecified or negative,
                 the label array of the return object is empty.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span></h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameters">
<li class="tsd-parameter">
<h5>dataset<wbr/>Data<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5></li>

data must not be normalized, otherwise some operations
of the model will fail.</p>

<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> <span>add<wbr/>Label</span><a href="#addLabel" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="addLabel.addLabel-1">add<wbr/>Label<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span><a href="#addLabel.addLabel-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> 
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Gets the current array of labels from a dataset and append a new
label according to the number of classes <a href="data.DataOffsetPosition.html#numClasses">numClasses</a>.
If there is one class, [0] means human and [1] bot while with
two classes, [1,0] means human and [0,1] bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>datasetLabels: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The current dataset label array, we add an element to it.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class, 0 for human and 1 for bot.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-inherited"><a id="loadDataSet" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set</span><a href="#loadDataSet" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-inherited">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1">load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>recorder<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span><a href="#loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>This method gets a recorder object and loads it as a Dataset object
with the right format. The return value might contain empty arrays if the
recorder as too few elements. The userIndex is an integer that says what is the
class index for the label, in our case of binary classifier human-bot, 0 means
human and 1 means bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>recorder: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The recorder containing loaded records and features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = -1</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class from record, if unspecified or negative,
                 the label array of the return object is empty.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span></h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameters">
<li class="tsd-parameter">
<h5>dataset<wbr/>Data<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5></li>
<li class="tsd-parameter">

<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-protected tsd-is-inherited">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="addLabel.addLabel-1">add<wbr/>Label<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">void</span><a href="#addLabel.addLabel-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagProtected">Protected</code> 
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Gets the current array of labels from a dataset and append a new
label according to the number of classes <a href="data.DataSimplePosition.html#numClasses">numClasses</a>.
If there is one class, [0] means human and [1] bot while with
two classes, [1,0] means human and [0,1] bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>datasetLabels: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The current dataset label array, we add an element to it.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class, 0 for human and 1 for bot.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-inherited"><a id="loadDataSet" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set</span><a href="#loadDataSet" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class tsd-is-inherited">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1">load<wbr/>Data<wbr/>Set<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>recorder<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, userIndex<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span><a href="#loadDataSet.loadDataSet-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>This method gets a recorder object and loads it as a Dataset object
with the right format. The return value might contain empty arrays if the
recorder as too few elements. The userIndex is an integer that says what is the
class index for the label, in our case of binary classifier human-bot, 0 means
human and 1 means bot.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>recorder: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The recorder containing loaded records and features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>userIndex: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = -1</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The index of the class from record, if unspecified or negative,
                 the label array of the return object is empty.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetData<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>datasetLabels<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span></h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameters">
<li class="tsd-parameter">

<li><a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a></li></ul>
<h1>Class Model&lt;G&gt;<code class="tsd-tag ts-flagAbstract">Abstract</code> </h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An abstract class that represents a model with its associated data used during the
training. Concretely, you can give to the constructor a way to load a
model with <a href="recording.Model.html#getModel">getModel</a> and describe how to use this model to in method
<a href="recording.Model.html#predict">predict</a> with parsed data from the given record and <a href="../modules/data.html">data</a>.
<br>
The model never loads if you never call <a href="recording.Model.html#getModel">getModel</a>, so you can instantiate
this class multiple times without troubles.</p>
</div></section>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="getModel" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagAbstract">Abstract</code> <span>get<wbr/>Model</span><a href="#getModel" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>

<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="getModel.getModel-1">get<wbr/>Model<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Type parameter">G</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span><a href="#getModel.getModel-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Loads the model (if it has never been done before) and returns it.</p>

<h3>Returns</h3><p>A promise of the loaded model.</p>
</div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Type parameter">G</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/recording.ts#L212">src/recording.ts:212</a></li></ul></aside></li></ul></section>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="predict" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagAbstract">Abstract</code> <span>predict</span><a href="#predict" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="predict.predict-1">predict<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>record<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, uniqueDataset<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span><a href="#predict.predict-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Given a record of mouse features, use both <a href="../modules/data.html">data</a> and <a href="recording.Model.html#model">model</a> fields to
format the record and predict a list of values, each element is a probability corresponding to
an element of the dataset to be a bot trajectory.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>record: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The record object with computed mouse features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>uniqueDataset: <span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An optional boolean, if true then we reshape the dataset to have a single
                     element with all our data, so the returned list should have a single element
                     (a single prediction), otherwise the model predict element by element and returns
                     the prediction array. All models do not support modified input shape.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>

<h1>Class RandomForestModel</h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An implementation of <a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a> for Random Forest classifiers.
The loadingPath is directly sent to loadFile then parsed to
JSON format and loaded with RandomForestClassifier.load.</p>

<h3>See</h3><p>Model</p>
</div></section>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="predict" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>predict</span><a href="#predict" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="predict.predict-1">predict<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>record<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, uniqueDataset<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span><a href="#predict.predict-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Given a record of mouse features, use both <a href="../modules/data.html">data</a> and <a href="recording.RandomForestModel.html#model">model</a> fields to
format the record and predict a list of values, each element is a probability corresponding to
an element of the dataset to be a bot trajectory.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>record: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The record object with computed mouse features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>uniqueDataset: <span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An optional boolean, if true then we reshape the dataset to have a single
                     element with all our data, so the returned list should have a single element
                     (a single prediction), otherwise the model predict element by element and returns
                     the prediction array. All models do not support modified input shape.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<p>Overrides <a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a>.<a href="recording.Model.html#predict">predict</a></p>
<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/recording.ts#L302">src/recording.ts:302</a></li></ul></aside></li></ul></section></section></div>

<div class="tsd-page-title">

<li><a href="../modules.html">@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse</a></li>

<li><a href="recording.Recorder.html">Recorder</a></li></ul>
<h1>Class Recorder</h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Recorder class to keep track of previously recorded mouse actions, mainly for move events.
It automatically computes all mouse features needed for <a href="data.Data.html">Data</a> format.
<br>
A simple usage would be to</p>
<ol>
    <li>add an event listener for mousemove or touchmove event;</li>
    <li>call <a href="recording.Recorder.html#addRecord">addRecord</a> with the timestamp and (x,y) coordinates every time the event fires;</li>
    <li>call <a href="recording.Recorder.html#isHuman">isHuman</a> with a preloaded model to know if the trajectory is from human or not.</li>
</ol>
Which gives something like :
```
recorder = new Recorder(window.screen.width, window.screen.height);
document.addEventListener("mousemove", event => {
  recorder.addRecord({
    time: event.timeStamp,
    x: event.clientX,
    y: event.clientY,
    type: "Move" // optional, not used in practice
  });

<p>  if (recorder.getRecords().length &gt; 100) {
      const isHuman = recorder.isHuman(delbot.Models.rnn3);
      recorder.clearRecord();
      // ...
  }
});</p>
<p>```
Be careful not to call <code>getPrediction</code> or <code>isHuman</code> too often, these may be heavy for smaller
configurations.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-hierarchy">

If the maxSize is reached, new elements shift the entire array and are added to the end.</p>

<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>add<wbr/>Record</span><a href="#addRecord" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>

<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="addRecord.addRecord-1">add<wbr/>Record<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>line<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="../interfaces/recording.SingleRecord.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Interface">SingleRecord</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a><a href="#addRecord.addRecord-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Add a line to the current record and calculate all mouse features.
You don&#39;t have to normalize the x and y components, it is done automatically
with the normalizer from the constructor.</p>

<h3>Returns</h3><p>The same recorder instance for chain calls.</p>
</div>

<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The recorded action that must contain at least timestamp, x and y positions.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="getPrediction" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>get<wbr/>Prediction</span><a href="#getPrediction" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="getPrediction.getPrediction-1">get<wbr/>Prediction<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>model<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Model.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Model</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">any</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span>, uniqueDataset<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span><a href="#getPrediction.getPrediction-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>This function takes a model <a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a> containing a TensorFlow.js layer model
and a <a href="data.Data.html">Data</a> instance and returns the list of probabilities for each batch
element to be a bot trajectory. The batch is obtained from <a href="recording.Recorder.html#currentRecord">currentRecord</a>.
<br>
This function may be heavy for smaller configurations, be careful not to call it too often.</p>

<h3>Returns</h3><p>A list of probabilities, empty list if is not enough datas.</p>

<h3>See</h3><p>isHuman</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>model: <a href="recording.Model.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Model</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">any</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>A <a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a> instance, with at least <code>predict()</code>.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>uniqueDataset: <span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = false</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Default to false, if true then all datasets are merged into one unique,
                     so there is one prediction and the average is its unique value.
                     Might throw error if the classifier doesn&#39;t support it.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/recording.ts#L603">src/recording.ts:603</a></li></ul></aside></li></ul></section>
