<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/recording.ts#L460">src/recording.ts:460</a></li></ul></aside></li></ul></section>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="isHuman" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>is<wbr/>Human</span><a href="#isHuman" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="isHuman.isHuman-1">is<wbr/>Human<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>model<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Model.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Model</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">any</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span>, threshold<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span>, uniqueDataset<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span>, consoleInfo<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><a href="../interfaces/recording.Result.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Interface">Result</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span><a href="#isHuman.isHuman-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>This function takes a model <a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a> containing a TensorFlow.js layer model
and a <a href="data.Data.html">Data</a> instance and returns whether the trajectory stored in
<a href="recording.Recorder.html#currentRecord">currentRecord</a> is considered as human or bot for the model.
<br>
There may be more than one input batch for the prediction, leading to more than
one probability <code>p</code> for the sample to be a bot. It consequently takes the average
of those probabilities and returns <code>true</code> if the average is less than a given threshold.
<br>
If there is not enough input data, so we have a batch size of 0, it returns
<code>false</code> and a reason <a href="recording.Recorder.html#notEnoughProvidedData">notEnoughProvidedData</a>.
<br>
This function may be heavy for smaller configurations, be careful not to call it too often.</p>

<h3>Returns</h3><p>A promise of an instance of <a href="../interfaces/recording.Result.html">Result</a> with two fields:</p>
<ul>
    <li>result, the boolean `true` iff it is a human trajectory</li>
    <li>reason of the return, set to <a href="recording.Recorder.html#notEnoughProvidedData">notEnoughProvidedData</a> if there is not enough data.</li>
</ul>
<h3>See</h3><p>getPrediction</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>model: <a href="recording.Model.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Model</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">any</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>A <a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a> instance, with at least <code>getData()</code> and <code>getModel()</code>.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>threshold: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = 0.2</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>A number between 0 and 1, if the average probability to be a bot is less
                 than this value, we consider the trajectory as human.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>uniqueDataset: <span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = false</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Default to false, if true then all datasets are merged into one unique,
                     so there one prediction and the average is its unique value.
                     Might throw error if the classifier doesn&#39;t support it.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>consoleInfo: <span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = false</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Default to false, if true then it prints the prediction to console.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><a href="../interfaces/recording.Result.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Interface">Result</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/recording.ts#L634">src/recording.ts:634</a></li></ul></aside></li></ul></section>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="loadRecordsFromString" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>load<wbr/>Records<wbr/>From<wbr/>String</span><a href="#loadRecordsFromString" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="loadRecordsFromString.loadRecordsFromString-1">load<wbr/>Records<wbr/>From<wbr/>String<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>recordString<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">string</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> | </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">string</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span>, xScale<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span>, yScale<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a><a href="#loadRecordsFromString.loadRecordsFromString-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Load an entire trajectory as string or string array into this <a href="recording.Recorder.html">Recorder</a>
instance. If the given input is a string, we split it with the separator <code>\n</code>.
The string array must be of the following format :</p>
<pre><code><span class="hl-1">[</span><span class="hl-9">&quot;resolution:1536,864&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-9">&quot;9131.1,Pressed,717,361&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-9">&quot;9134.8,Move,717,361&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-9">&quot;9151.8,Move,717,361&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-1">...</span><br/><span class="hl-9">&quot;10402.3,Move,722,360&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-9">&quot;10419.1,Move,718,358&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-9">&quot;10425.8,Released,717,360]&quot;</span>
</code></pre>
<p>As first line we have the screen resolution to normalize
X and Y and all other lines are <code>timestamp,actionType,x,y</code>.
We then add each line with <a href="recording.Recorder.html#addRecord">addRecord</a>.
<br>
Notice that the instance is cleared with <a href="recording.Recorder.html#clearRecord">clearRecord</a> when calling
this method and the first line with resolution is optional, if absent,
we keep the previous normalizers (1 if unspecified in constructor).</p>

<h3>Returns</h3><p>The same recorder instance for chain calls.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>recordString: <span class="tsd-signature-type">string</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> | </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">string</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The string describing the trajectory.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>xScale: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = -1</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>If specified and &gt; 0, the x normalization will be this value.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>yScale: <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = -1</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>If specified and &gt; 0, the y normalization will be this value.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/recording.ts#L559">src/recording.ts:559</a></li></ul></aside></li></ul></section>

<h1>Class TensorFlowModel</h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An implementation of <a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a> for TensorFlow layers models.
The loadingPath is directly sent to tf.loadLayersModel and leads to
the json file of the model.</p>

<h3>See</h3><p>Model</p>
</div></section>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-hierarchy">
<h4>Hierarchy</h4>
<ul class="tsd-hierarchy">

<section class="tsd-panel-group tsd-index-group">
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-index-panel">
<details class="tsd-index-content tsd-index-accordion" open><summary class="tsd-accordion-summary tsd-index-summary">

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class"><a id="predict" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>predict</span><a href="#predict" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<ul class="tsd-signatures tsd-kind-method tsd-parent-kind-class">
<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="predict.predict-1">predict<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>record<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a>, uniqueDataset<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span><a href="#predict.predict-1" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></li>
<li class="tsd-description">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Given a record of mouse features, use both <a href="../modules/data.html">data</a> and <a href="recording.TensorFlowModel.html#model">model</a> fields to
format the record and predict a list of values, each element is a probability corresponding to
an element of the dataset to be a bot trajectory.</p>
</div>
<div class="tsd-parameters">
<h4 class="tsd-parameters-title">Parameters</h4>
<ul class="tsd-parameter-list">
<li>
<h5>record: <a href="recording.Recorder.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">Recorder</a></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The record object with computed mouse features.</p>
</div></li>
<li>
<h5>uniqueDataset: <span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = false</span></h5>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>An optional boolean, if true then we reshape the dataset to have a single
                     element with all our data, so the returned list should have a single element
                     (a single prediction), otherwise the model predict element by element and returns
                     the prediction array. All models do not support modified input shape.</p>
</div></li></ul></div>
<h4 class="tsd-returns-title">Returns <span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">[]</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span></h4><aside class="tsd-sources">
<p>Overrides <a href="recording.Model.html">Model</a>.<a href="recording.Model.html#predict">predict</a></p>
<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/recording.ts#L241">src/recording.ts:241</a></li></ul></aside></li></ul></section></section></div>

<section class="tsd-panel">

<li class="tsd-signature tsd-anchor-link" id="loadFile">load<wbr/>File<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">(</span>filePath<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">string</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">)</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><span class="tsd-signature-type">Promise</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-type">string</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span><a href="#loadFile" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none" id="icon-anchor-a"></path><path d="M10 14a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 5 0l4 -4a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 -5 -5l-.5 .5" id="icon-anchor-b"></path><path d="M14 10a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 -5 0l-4 4a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 5 5l.5 -.5" id="icon-anchor-c"></path></svg></a></li>

<div class="col-8 col-content">
<div class="tsd-page-title">
<h2>@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse</h2></div>
<div class="tsd-panel tsd-typography">
<a href="#deep-learning-for-bot-detection-by-mouse-movements-delbot-mouse" id="deep-learning-for-bot-detection-by-mouse-movements-delbot-mouse" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h1>DEep Learning for BOT detection by Mouse movements (DELBOT Mouse)</h1>
</a>
<p>This repository is a small TypeScript library to distinguish humans and bots from their mouse movements with
the usage of <a href="https://www.tensorflow.org/js">TensorFlow.js</a>. It was initiated by an internship with the
<a href="https://www.bureau404.fr">Bureau404</a> company as part of the Master&#39;s in Mathematics:
Specialist Focus on Careers in Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence (<a href="https://web.umons.ac.be/fr/">University of Mons</a>)</p>
<ul>
<li>Author : Christophe Grandmont.</li>
<li>Internship supervisor (Bureau404) : Loïc Jean-Fulcrand (<a href="https://www.malt.ch/profile/loicjeanfulcrand">website</a>)</li>
<li>Internship supervisor (UMONS) : Christophe Troestler (<a href="https://staff.umons.ac.be/christophe.troestler/">website</a>)</li>
</ul>

<a href="#about" id="about" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h2>About</h2>
</a>
<p>Delbot Mouse is a prototype open-source tool using <a href="https://www.tensorflow.org/js">TensorFlow.js</a> and some more
other libraries like RandomForest to develop a generic way to distinguish humans and bots from their mouse movements on
a web page. The repository contains three distinct JavaScript or Typescript modules:</p>
<ol>
<li>delbot-core: the core of the library that contains everything to load an existing model and use it.</li>
<li>delbot-training: the part of the code using delbot-core to train new models from scratch. It also contains a 
Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) implementation to generate bot trajectories.</li>
<li>delbot-example: example of usage of delbot-core and delbot-training to train new models or use one.</li>
</ol>
<p>We also have a <code>python/</code> folder being the script location to manipulate data.</p>
<p>Delbot-core:
<a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse?color=33cd56&logo=npm" alt="npm version"></a></p>
<p>Delbot-training:
<a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@chrisgdt/delbot-training"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/@chrisgdt/delbot-training?color=33cd56&logo=npm" alt="npm version"></a></p>

<a href="#how-to-install" id="how-to-install" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h2>How to install</h2>
</a>

<a href="#for-node" id="for-node" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h3>For Node</h3>
</a>
<p>You can install delbot-core or delbot-training from NPM for Node with:</p>
<pre><code><span class="hl-0">npm</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-0">install</span><span class="hl-1"> @</span><span class="hl-0">chrisgdt</span><span class="hl-1">/</span><span class="hl-0">delbot</span><span class="hl-1">-</span><span class="hl-0">mouse</span>
</code></pre>
<pre><code><span class="hl-0">npm</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-0">install</span><span class="hl-1"> @</span><span class="hl-0">chrisgdt</span><span class="hl-1">/</span><span class="hl-0">delbot</span><span class="hl-1">-</span><span class="hl-0">training</span>
</code></pre>
<p>You will also need to install TensorFlow, we let you chose the version.</p>
<pre><code><span class="hl-0">npm</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-0">install</span><span class="hl-1"> @</span><span class="hl-0">tensorflow</span><span class="hl-1">/</span><span class="hl-0">tfjs</span>
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Notice that Delbot Mouse is initially meant to be used in the web browser</strong>. Using Node.js or other
JavaScript engines might lead to some unknown errors that you can report here as issue.</p>

<a href="#for-the-browser" id="for-the-browser" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h3>For the browser</h3>
</a>
<p>For a browser usage, you can simply add some script tags. To load delbot-mouse, you need TensorFlow.js.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html"><span class="hl-2">&lt;</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-4"> </span><span class="hl-5">src</span><span class="hl-4">=</span><span class="hl-6">&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tensorflow/tfjs@4.0.0/dist/tf.min.js&quot;</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;</span><br/><span class="hl-2">&lt;</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-4"> </span><span class="hl-5">src</span><span class="hl-4">=</span><span class="hl-6">&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse@1.1.2/dist/delbot.js&quot;</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;</span>
</code></pre>
<p>To load  delbot-training, you need both Tensorflow.js and delbot-training, and it is highly encouraged to load tfjs-vis
for training visualization.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html"><span class="hl-2">&lt;</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-4"> </span><span class="hl-5">src</span><span class="hl-4">=</span><span class="hl-6">&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tensorflow/tfjs@4.0.0/dist/tf.min.js&quot;</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;</span><br/><span class="hl-2">&lt;</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-4"> </span><span class="hl-5">src</span><span class="hl-4">=</span><span class="hl-6">&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tensorflow/tfjs-vis@1.5.1/dist/tfjs-vis.umd.min.js&quot;</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;</span><br/><span class="hl-2">&lt;</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-4"> </span><span class="hl-5">src</span><span class="hl-4">=</span><span class="hl-6">&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse@1.1.2/dist/delbot.js&quot;</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;</span><br/><span class="hl-2">&lt;</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-4"> </span><span class="hl-5">src</span><span class="hl-4">=</span><span class="hl-6">&quot; https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@chrisgdt/delbot-training@1.1.2/dist/delbot-training.js&quot;</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="hl-3">script</span><span class="hl-2">&gt;</span>
</code></pre>

<a href="#how-to-use" id="how-to-use" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h2>How to use</h2>
</a>
<p>With Node, you can import delbot with <code>import * as delbot from &quot;@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse&quot;;</code>.</p>
<p>If needed, you can also import tensorFlow with <code>import * as tf from &#39;@tensorflow/tfjs&#39;;</code>.</p>
<p>To import delbot-training, use <code>import * as delbotrain from &quot;@chrisgdt/delbot-training&quot;;</code>.</p>
<hr>
<p>For browser, once you have loaded delbot mouse with the script tag, everything is packed in the single variable
<code>delbot</code>, same for the variable <code>delbotrain</code> with delbot-training. Everything is exported from <code>src/index.ts</code>, check the
<a href="https://chrisgdt.github.io/DELBOT-Mouse/delbot-core/docs/modules/index.html">doc of delbot-core</a> or the
<a href="https://chrisgdt.github.io/DELBOT-Mouse/delbot-training/docs/modules/index.html">doc of delbot-training</a> for more information.</p>
<p>The folder <code>trained-models/</code> contains some pre-trained models that you can use easily from delbot-core with, for example,
<code>delbot.Models.rnn3</code>.</p>
<p>Otherwise, you have an entire example of usage without the training in <code>/delbot-example/</code> <a href="https://chrisgdt.github.io/DELBOT-Mouse/delbot-example/src/index.html">here</a>.</p>

<a href="#basic-usage---example" id="basic-usage---example" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h2>Basic usage - Example</h2>
</a>
<pre><code class="language-ts"><span class="hl-7">import</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-8">*</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-7">as</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-0">delbot</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-7">from</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-9">&quot;@chrisgdt/delbot-mouse&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">; </span><span class="hl-10">// not needed in browser</span><br/><br/><span class="hl-10">// Create an empty recorder to store and compute mouse features</span><br/><span class="hl-10">// Set the screen size to normalize (x,y) positions in [0,1]^2</span><br/><span class="hl-0">recorder</span><span class="hl-1"> = </span><span class="hl-8">new</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-11">Recorder</span><span class="hl-1">(</span><span class="hl-0">window</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">screen</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">width</span><span class="hl-1">, </span><span class="hl-0">window</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">screen</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">height</span><span class="hl-1">);</span><br/><br/><span class="hl-10">// Set max size to prevent high memory usage</span><br/><span class="hl-0">recorder</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-11">setMaxSize</span><span class="hl-1">(</span><span class="hl-12">1e6</span><span class="hl-1">);</span><br/><br/><span class="hl-10">// For each small movement, store it in the recorder</span><br/><span class="hl-0">document</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-11">addEventListener</span><span class="hl-1">(</span><span class="hl-9">&quot;mousemove&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">, </span><span class="hl-0">event</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-8">=&gt;</span><span class="hl-1"> {</span><br/><span class="hl-1">  </span><span class="hl-0">recorder</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-11">addRecord</span><span class="hl-1">({</span><br/><span class="hl-1">    </span><span class="hl-0">time:</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-0">event</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">timeStamp</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-1">    </span><span class="hl-0">x:</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-0">event</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">clientX</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-1">    </span><span class="hl-0">y:</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-0">event</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">clientY</span><span class="hl-1">,</span><br/><span class="hl-1">    </span><span class="hl-0">type:</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-9">&quot;Move&quot;</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-10">// optional</span><br/><span class="hl-1">  });</span><br/><span class="hl-1">});</span><br/><br/><span class="hl-0">myVerifyElement</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-11">addEventListener</span><span class="hl-1">(</span><span class="hl-9">&quot;click&quot;</span><span class="hl-1">, </span><span class="hl-0">event</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-8">=&gt;</span><span class="hl-1"> {</span><br/><span class="hl-1">  </span><span class="hl-7">if</span><span class="hl-1"> (</span><span class="hl-0">recorder</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-11">getRecords</span><span class="hl-1">().</span><span class="hl-0">length</span><span class="hl-1"> &gt; </span><span class="hl-12">100</span><span class="hl-1">) {</span><br/><span class="hl-1">    </span><span class="hl-10">// Models are obtained from delbot.Models</span><br/><span class="hl-1">    </span><span class="hl-8">const</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-13">isHuman</span><span class="hl-1"> = </span><span class="hl-0">recorder</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-11">isHuman</span><span class="hl-1">(</span><span class="hl-0">delbot</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">Models</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">rnn1</span><span class="hl-1">);</span><br/><span class="hl-1">    </span><span class="hl-0">recorder</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-11">clearRecord</span><span class="hl-1">();</span><br/><span class="hl-1">    </span><span class="hl-10">// ...</span><br/><span class="hl-1">  }</span><br/><span class="hl-1">});</span>
</code></pre>

<a href="#training" id="training" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h2>Training</h2>
</a>
<p>Here some example and explanations about the training of new models.</p>

<a href="#models" id="models" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h3>Models</h3>
</a>
<p>Some pre-trained models are available through <code>delbot.Models</code> :</p>
<ul>
<li>rnn1 : a neural network with two LSTM layers, the most efficient so far.</li>
<li>rrn1faster : same, but with less LSTM cells, slightly less efficient.</li>
<li>rnn2 : same, but the second LSTM layer is replaced by a dense layer.</li>
<li>rnn3 : a model between rnn1 and rnn3, two LSTM layers then one dense.</li>
<li>denseMatrix : a neural network with only dense layers and that takes a movement matrix.</li>
<li>convolutional : a convolutional model that takes a movement matrix.</li>
<li>randomForest : a random forest machine learning model.</li>
</ul>
<p>To train your own model with custom tfjs layers, you can look at <code>delbot-training/src/models.ts</code> and read
the documentation. You only have to extend a class and define a single method.</p>
<p>You also have a GAN architecture in <code>delbot-training/src/GANtrain.ts</code>.</p>

<a href="#dataset" id="dataset" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h3>Dataset</h3>
</a>
<p>To manipulate the dataset, you can use <code>python/</code> folder, here is a short description of each python script.</p>
<ul>
<li>parseSample.py : takes some folders with text files of either bot or human trajectories and parse them to a single
          session.json file containing all relative paths to those text files. This JSON file is the entry
          of an instance of dataTraining.</li>
<li>redraw.py : verifies that text trajectories in a folder is what we except by drawing them with matplotlib.</li>
<li>botDrawing.py : starts python selenium and draw same shapes from arbitrary heuristics and multiple librairies.</li>
<li>ganParser.py : takes some GAN folder of generator ouputs and parse them to something readable by <code>parseSample.py</code>.</li>
</ul>
<p>For the dataset usage in the training itself, unzip the file <code>dataset.tar.gz</code> to obtain multiple data folder inside
<code>python/</code>, then run <code>parseSample.py</code> to get <code>sessions.json</code> (for normal training) and <code>sessions_human_only.json</code> (for GAN).</p>

<a href="#example" id="example" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">
  <h3>Example</h3>
</a>
<p>The code of a basic training looks like this :</p>
<pre><code class="language-ts"><span class="hl-8">const</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-13">data</span><span class="hl-1"> = </span><span class="hl-8">new</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-0">delbot</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-0">data</span><span class="hl-1">.</span><span class="hl-11">DataFeatures2</span><span class="hl-1">({</span><span class="hl-0">xSize:</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-12">24</span><span class="hl-1">, </span><span class="hl-0">numClasses:</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-12">2</span><span class="hl-1">});</span><br/><span class="hl-8">const</span><span class="hl-1"> </span><span class="hl-13">filePath</span><span class="hl-1"> = </span><span <h1>Interface Result</h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Represents the result of the model to decide whether the record was human or not.
It&#39;s simply a boolean with a reason, i.e. small description of the result.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-hierarchy">

<div class="tsd-signature">reason<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">:</span> <span class="tsd-signature-type">Symbol</span></div>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>One of the three static field of Recorder class :</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="../classes/recording.Recorder.html#success">success</a> if the record was considered as human.</li>
  <li><a href="../classes/recording.Recorder.html#fail">fail</a> if the record was considered as bot.</li>
  <li><a href="../classes/recording.Recorder.html#notEnoughProvidedData">notEnoughProvidedData</a> if there were not enough provided data.</li>
</ul></div><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-property tsd-parent-kind-interface"><a id="result" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>result</span><a href="#result" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<div class="tsd-signature">result<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">:</span> <span class="tsd-signature-type">boolean</span></div>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The simple boolean, true if the recording was considered as human. Otherwise,
the <a href="recording.Result.html#reason">reason</a> gives more details.</p>

<h1>Interface SingleRecord</h1></div>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-comment">
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Represent a generic instance of a single recorded mouse action. It must contain at least
three data : time, x and y. Other features are calculated from these three data
in the Recorder class.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-hierarchy">
<h4>Hierarchy</h4>
<ul class="tsd-hierarchy">

<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagOptional">Optional</code> <span>accel</span><a href="#accel" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none" id="icon-anchor-a"></path><path d="M10 14a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 5 0l4 -4a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 -5 -5l-.5 .5" id="icon-anchor-b"></path><path d="M14 10a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 -5 0l-4 4a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 5 5l.5 -.5" id="icon-anchor-c"></path></svg></a></h3>
<div class="tsd-signature">accel<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?:</span> <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></div>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The total acceleration between the current point and the previous one,
calculated the difference of two consecutive speed divided by <code>dt</code>.</p>
</div><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>
<li>Defined in <a href="https://github.com/chrisgdt/DELBOT-Mouse/blob/9be94c7/delbot-core/src/recording.ts#L86">src/recording.ts:86</a></li></ul></aside></section>
<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-property tsd-parent-kind-interface"><a id="accelX" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagOptional">Optional</code> <span>accelX</span><a href="#accelX" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<div class="tsd-signature">accelX<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?:</span> <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></div>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The acceleration in X axis between the current point and the previous one, calculated with
the difference of two consecutive speed x divided by <code>dt</code>.</p>
</div><aside class="tsd-sources">

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-property tsd-parent-kind-interface"><a id="type" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><code class="tsd-tag ts-flagOptional">Optional</code> <span>type</span><a href="#type" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<div class="tsd-signature">type<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">?:</span> <span class="tsd-signature-type">string</span></div>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The type of the recorded movement, it can be &quot;Pressed&quot;, &quot;Released&quot; or &quot;Move&quot; (ending with &quot;Touch&quot; if from
a mobile device). It isn&#39;t actually used, so it can be undefined.</p>
</div><aside class="tsd-sources">

<section class="tsd-panel tsd-member tsd-kind-property tsd-parent-kind-interface"><a id="x" class="tsd-anchor"></a>
<h3 class="tsd-anchor-link"><span>x</span><a href="#x" aria-label="Permalink" class="tsd-anchor-icon"><svg class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-link" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><use href="#icon-anchor-a"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-b"></use><use href="#icon-anchor-c"></use></svg></a></h3>
<div class="tsd-signature">x<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">:</span> <span class="tsd-signature-type">number</span></div>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>The pixel of the x position of the movement. If used with a normalization where the scale is the
screen resolution, it is a number between 0 and 1, where 0 represents the left side and 1 the right side.</p>
</div><aside class="tsd-sources">
<ul>

<h1>Variable Models<code class="tsd-tag ts-flagConst">Const</code> </h1></div>
<div class="tsd-signature">Models<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">:</span> <span class="tsd-signature-type">Readonly</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&lt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">{ </span><br/><span>    </span>convolutional<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="../classes/recording.TensorFlowModel.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">TensorFlowModel</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>denseMatrix<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="../classes/recording.TensorFlowModel.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">TensorFlowModel</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>randomForest<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="../classes/recording.RandomForestModel.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">RandomForestModel</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>rnn1<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="../classes/recording.TensorFlowModel.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">TensorFlowModel</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span>    </span>rnn3<span class="tsd-signature-symbol">: </span><a href="../classes/recording.TensorFlowModel.html" class="tsd-signature-type" data-tsd-kind="Class">TensorFlowModel</a><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">; </span><br/><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">}</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol">&gt;</span><span class="tsd-signature-symbol"> = ...</span></div>
<div class="tsd-comment tsd-typography"><p>Contains pre-trained models for an easy use of <a href="../modules/index.html#Model">Model</a> class with <a href="../modules/index.html#Recorder">Recorder</a>.
The best model so far is rnn1.</p>
